IvtiwymVjdata6aQmg6fVbcKndZY5iwF7d5vg_y2gOvbdZmV7eZx6QcxgsbGiGRvFDeQNqqJzAuyc6izd5qbwp_3zGyIwcYH6X58epJbXGgJMN\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Java test rules**\\n\\nI need to follow the rule to keep coverage for each dynamic-access class in its dedicated Java test file. ShellConsoleTest is a start. I'm considering using URLClassLoader for public dynamic loading since it might not be supported otherwise. There’s a guideline for when to catch UnsupportedFeatureError and rethrow it. However, if native image support is limited, the v1 coverage from child loading won’t work. The tests should run under a native image by default and handle unsupported scenarios correctly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Configuring JLine dependencies**\\n\\nI’m considering whether to add JLine1 as a detached file and how to locate the jar for testing. Gradle could manage both versions, so I might set up configurations like `jline1Runtime` and `jline2Runtime` in build.gradle. The test class could refer to system properties for file paths. I wonder if that’s over-complicated. An easier idea might be using Gradle to resolve the old JLine jar and expose its path, while ensuring that the child loader incorporates the necessary jars.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering JLine and native image**\\n\\nI’m thinking that the native-image code source might behave oddly, while the JVM seems fine. I need to establish a property for the JLine1 jar path in the test. Using a custom URLClassLoader with a null parent could prevent access to app classes like jline2 or Rhino, but I wonder if that complicates things. It seems like I'll need a JDK to properly execute this setup. Overall, I’m trying to keep things straightforward.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Verifying NativeImageSupport**\\n\\nI'm checking on NativeImageSupport. It seems I need to compile with helper classes for jline1 and jline2. However, if the test runtime classpath includes jline1 config and not in testRuntimeClasspath, that could be an issue. The URLClassLoader might reference a jar path at runtime, but native can't load that. I believe dynamic-access coverage for native image metadata probably comes from JVM tests. So, I’ll need to include jline1 URL as a system property.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_xxp1DSbyc2uFFQzcTuXK7qz7|fc_03a0661c95551787016a2741115a008193a08ab2a6ed7a76d2", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/java/org_mozilla/rhino/ShellConsoleTest.java", "offset": 1, "limit": 240}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 5252, "output": 2203, "cacheRead": 32256, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39711, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780957401669, "responseId": "resp_03a0661c95551787016a2740da62548193bc0d0ea22d365bc0"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_xxp1DSbyc2uFFQzcTuXK7qz7|fc_03a0661c95551787016a2741115a008193a08ab2a6ed7a76d2", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_mozilla.rhino;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.Context;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.Scriptable;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.tools.shell.ShellConsole;\n\npublic class ShellConsoleTest {\n    @Test\n    void createsJLineConsoleAndInvokesOutputOperations() throws Exception {\n        String previousTerminal = System.getProperty(\"jline.terminal\");\n        System.setProperty(\"jline.terminal\", \"jline.UnsupportedTerminal\");\n        Context context = Context.enter();\n        try {\n            Scriptable scope = context.initStandardObjects();\n\n            ShellConsole console = ShellConsole.getConsole(scope, StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n\n            assertThat(console).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(console.getIn()).isNotNull();\n            console.print(\"alpha\");\n            console.println(\"beta\");\n            console.println();\n            console.flush();\n        } finally {\n            Context.exit();\n            restoreSystemProperty(\"jline.terminal\", previousTerminal);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void restoreSystemProperty(String key, String previousValue) {\n        if (previousValue == null) {\n            System.clearProperty(key);\n        } else {\n            System.setProperty(key, previousValue);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780957457903}]}
