[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating class loading issues**\n\nI'm thinking about the outer load issue. If I use a nested public class and include the full test runtime classpath URLs, it seems the outer class can load all dependencies. It looks like I need a child-first approach for the nested class, while the outer might be loaded by URLClassLoader. Dependencies could be all in the URLs or the parent. I must ensure to avoid an extra top-level helper, but the current package-private setup is inaccessible.\n\n**Clarifying constructor accessibility**\n\nI’m thinking about whether a class without a constructor still has a default constructor. According to the Java Language Specification, the default constructor does indeed have the same accessibility as the class itself. So, if it's a public nested class, the default constructor is public as well. That clears things up! I just need to make sure to edit accordingly based on this understanding.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_03a0661c95551787016a2741a68e888193857540ff56ab6fdc\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJ0G8uALaE0UJQLCwAkPMFzKVS5YfCeK_c7sZyU3yG0oDL9p70XWK68bBMlvV_fOtiEsPDe-Os9BgN4qQAV_b-kO9PbrGuY7mZ9tlOgxFLtrmsOpC6jLkdu4jl1xpiCi5vcPqRqKav85LlOn6yzE0EgACpcumFBN3HBxX_5ryGrxwW_gloSxGFM0eg5H6TEY_mta4CPP4C622qhz2flRydS8GVkNAdekrtRkvrc3Y7zYA-cX8merN_IGLpXlUcJiHKm2Q1o7uytYJd4S1I9LLXzIUjUp3ovksVrakpulssYDMqJQTsMBk96d09wU7_xcPIVGtrtzLqHDkYo4_opK6v9CcFTORJOIaPW8sYb-OIvPkrw8cQXTxDhutVQggXsw_UbpT7ajj05hxe1BviMakdUr0ebrGC2qhdhqxHVC1p64yZiL589xrcKu4vh_a5FOcUAFHvplYvXZwpH6dAu_j7A8T9W3M6GamrvGUSUXVXp1pwOO3LDfpbMLiLvTttQY5vYlAKH8rRchyE-mahEPoua-51-12DD8kisGQYJ9WvAgbz05rewRUKGhWfJeAp1CzrZ_acC4dzt_AKasASqxAura-wSKjnBlPdZSppPi_nzLgzjP_xAg_JbTEY-U2tu1YsMH8ptNDtqd9wI7aBwV-VdQYT2Pbmvk6HBLT0ASc_98R8dM5xU02HiUGFdgjxCt7RdIx-6xnJI9_EpYmu3hy6ENvbT5hK96eDm9_-oBrhoFIRc-81ROxybznmsWiZJqR5FLn2niMp2-tTHyyFt4fMCIXRruN6Qr