I'm thinking about the outer load issue. If I use a nested public class and include the full test runtime classpath URLs, it seems the outer class can load all dependencies. It looks like I need a child-first approach for the nested class, while the outer might be loaded by URLClassLoader. Dependencies could be all in the URLs or the parent. I must ensure to avoid an extra top-level helper, but the current package-private setup is inaccessible.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying constructor accessibility**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether a class without a constructor still has a default constructor. According to the Java Language Specification, the default constructor does indeed have the same accessibility as the class itself. So, if it's a public nested class, the default constructor is public as well. That clears things up! I just need to make sure to edit accordingly based on this understanding.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_0efkyUWJLClyPolXwf9FRlDc|fc_03a0661c95551787016a2741bc91b08193bc3d8adb597e805d", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/java/org_mozilla/rhino/ShellConsoleTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "        urls.add(codeSourceUrl(JLineVersion1ShellConsoleExercise.class));\n", "newText": "        urls.add(codeSourceUrl(JLineVersion1Exercise.class));\n"}, {"oldText": "                    JLineVersion1ShellConsoleExercise.class.getName(), true, loader);\n", "newText": "                    JLineVersion1Exercise.class.getName(), true, loader);\n"}, {"oldText": "                \"jline.\",\n                \"org.mozilla.\",\n                \"org_mozilla.rhino.JLineVersion1ShellConsoleExercise\"\n", "newText": "                \"jline.\",\n                \"org.mozilla.\",\n                \"org_mozilla.rhino.ShellConsoleTest$JLineVersion1Exercise\"\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static final class ChildFirstUrlClassLoader extends URLClassLoader {\n", "newText": "    public static final class JLineVersion1Exercise implements Callable<String> {\n        @Override\n        public String call() throws Exception {\n            String previousTerminal = System.getProperty(\"jline.terminal\");\n            System.setProperty(\"jline.terminal\", \"jline.UnsupportedTerminal\");\n            Context context = Context.enter();\n            try {\n                Scriptable scope = context.initStandardObjects();\n\n                ShellConsole console = ShellConsole.getConsole(scope, StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n                if (console == null) {\n                    throw new AssertionError(\"Expected a JLine v1 shell console\");\n                }\n                console.print(\"alpha\");\n                console.println(\"beta\");\n                console.println();\n                console.flush();\n                return console.getClass().getName();\n            } finally {\n                Context.exit();\n                if (previousTerminal == null) {\n                    System.clearProperty(\"jline.terminal\");\n                } else {\n                    System.setProperty(\"jline.terminal\", previousTerminal);\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class ChildFirstUrlClassLoader extends URLClassLoader {\n"}, {"oldText": "}\n\nfinal class JLineVersion1ShellConsoleExercise implements Callable<String> {\n    @Override\n    public String call() throws Exception {\n        String previousTerminal = System.getProperty(\"jline.terminal\");\n        System.setProperty(\"jline.terminal\", \"jline.UnsupportedTerminal\");\n        Context context = Context.enter();\n        try {\n            Scriptable scope = context.initStandardObjects();\n\n            ShellConsole console = ShellConsole.getConsole(scope, StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n            if (console == null) {\n                throw new AssertionError(\"Expected a JLine v1 shell console\");\n            }\n            console.print(\"alpha\");\n       